The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the transformation graph of $BR$-matchings. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses upper bounds and asymptotic analysis, which are common in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
